RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 13100. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 29. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250, i f for $6,000, allowed 2 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAR LADY was three wide into the first turn, settled in the back and moved to the inside, advanced nearing the half mile marker while saving ground, shifted out nearing the three eighths marker, advanced on the turn and came four wide into the lane, closed well under left handed crop urging and edged clear in the final seventy yards to prove best. MI CLEOPATRA AND I tracked the pace, made a two wide bid in hand to be clear by the quarter pole, widened the margin off the turn, but was caught in the final hundred yards while staying on to be clearly second best. LOVE IS STRONG was reserved early, three wide on the backstretch, came five wide into the lane and had a belated rally to best the rest. SWITCHRATTLENROLL was allowed to settle early, advanced two wide on the turn to be in contention by the quarter pole but weakened in the drive. DANCE A LITTLE JIG was reserved early, wide trip and had no rally. HAY BUCK was three wide into the first turn, then sprinted clear and got to the inside on the backstretch, then gave way nearing the quarter pole.

INNUENDO set the pace while racing off the inside in the two to three path, then was headed by the furlong marker and dug in gamely but could not go with winner while being clearly second best. MR BOLDACIOUS stalked the pace four wide, came five wide into the lane and ran on to best the rest. COUSIN BOB chased the pace five wide and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RIPKEN was allowed to settle early, made a four wide move nearing the quarter pole, continued that move when straightened in the lane and edged clear late to prove best, driving. HANFORD was reserved early two wide, dropped to the rail and advanced on the turn, then was blocked nearing the quarter pole, remained blocked on the rail to the three sixteenths marker, tacked out for racing room and finished well to gain the show award, tough trip. CITY OF GOD vied for the early lead on the inside, then rated back and stalked the pace on the inside, remained saving ground and faded in the lane, bested rest. UPTOWNJACOB BROWN got out into the first turn, corrected quickly, then trailed early, advanced on the turn and passed the tiring rivals. FIFTH ELEMENT stalked the early pace, then went up three wide and in between foes on the backstretch, weakened in the drive. SENSE OF IRELAND was not a factor. WHAT'S HIS NAME tracked the pace on the inside and stopped.

SIMPLE JUSTICE was settled back early, advanced on the inside on the turn, angled out in the furlong grounds and rallied well to gain the place award. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR PENNSYLVANIA BRED OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRENDING UP was void of early speed, advanced three wide on the turn, came four wide into the drive, closed fast to get up in time, driving. DEE JAY stumbled at the break, then recovered and went up to set a pressured fast pace on the inside, dug in gamely in the drive turning back multiple bids, drifted out late and was denied on the wire to just miss. FAMISHED pressed the early pace three wide, then was two wide on the turn, loomed boldly at the furlong marker but hung late. EAGLES CRY tracked the early pace in between rivals on the first turn, then made it to the inside, drafted behind the front runners on the inside on the turn, made a bid leaving the turn to loom by the furlong marker but needed more late. WILL E SUTTON chased the early pace on the inside, then settled on the backstretch, angled out leaving the turn and had a belated rally. TATE stalked the early pace three wide, then dropped back on the turn, weakened. YES SIR ROBERT was five wide into the first turn, chased the pace four wide and tired. The rider on the number five FAMISHED claimed foul against the number two DEE JAY for interference nearing the wire, after the STEWARDS reviewed the replays the OBJECTION was disallowed and race left as is.
